g.text: Endurance: You feel something in your chest. An unnatural pressure. It's spreading to your left arm, your jaw...
You: The end of the world is here.
Endurance: Don't think this is a sign of anything other than your heart failing.
Endurance: There's no shame in surrendering now. We all do, it gets *so* dark. You don't even see her face, like you always thought you would. You only see pain and fear.
Physical Instrument: Get it together, boy. You've gotta hold on, no matter how bad...
Endurance: Yeah, screaming isn't happening on account of extreme shortness of breath. You're just making it worse. Oh god, it's painful...
You: So I'm guessing this is bad.
You: I'm sure it's just heartburn. Oh god...
Endurance: Very. *Very* bad. *This is the end* bad.
Endurance: Nope, sorry, you don't. Not this time.
Half Light: Fucking shit, I'm scared. What do I do? Who do I call?
Endurance: All you feel is pain and weakness. You have to surrender now. We all do, it gets *so* dark. You don't even see her face, like you always thought you would. You only see pain and fear.
Savoir Faire: Well, this feels familiar.
Pain Threshold: We've been here before. You've got this.
Endurance: No. It's many years of combined self-neglect and self-abuse.
Composure: Don't go grabbing at your chest and screaming bloody murder. Keep your cool. Remember -- looking good always makes you feel better.
